Bank of Ireland, Linedata Services, Total: Europe Equity Preview

-- B y   V i c t o r i a   S t i l w e l l
-- 
2011-07-12T04:00:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-11/bank-of-ireland-linedata-services-total-europe-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in European trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses.  The Stoxx  Europe  600 Index dropped 1.4 percent to 269.90.
The Stoxx 50 Index fell 1.1 percent to 2,542.86. The Euro Stoxx
50 Index, a benchmark measure for nations using the euro,
decreased 2.9 percent to 2,709.14.  Bank of Ireland Plc (BKIR LN): The country’s largest bank
said today that all proposed resolutions at an extraordinary
general shareholders meeting were passed, including a resolution
to boost the bank’s capital. The stock plunged 9.7 percent to
10.1 euro cents.  Barclays Plc (BARC)  :  The lender’s call-options volume
jumped to the highest since February in the U.S. as investors
bet that the second-largest U.K. bank by assets will rebound
from a two-year low as European lenders prepare to release
stress-test results July 15. The stock dropped 3.8 percent to
233.95 pence.  Linedata Services (LIN)  :  France ’s largest maker of
financial software for leasing and credit companies said it
plans to buy Fimasys, a financial technology provider. The
shares were unchanged at 12.06 euros.  Publicis Groupe SA (PUB)  : The advertising company bought
70 percent of Brazilian agency DPZ, with an option to acquire
all of it. The shares declined 1.9 percent to 37.85 euros.  Royal Bank of Scotland Group Plc (RBS)  : Wells Fargo &
Co. and Royal Bank of  Scotland  are marketing $1.48 billion in
bonds backed by commercial mortgages, according to a person with
knowledge of the transaction. The shares fell 4 percent to 35.72
pence.  Stratex International Plc (STI)  : The London-based mining
company says Centamin Egypt Ltd.’s offer to acquire Stratex’s
joint-venture parter Sheba Exploration (UK) Plc is a “welcome
development.” The company commented in a statement. The stock
rose 1.9 percent to 8.2 pence.  Tonnellerie Francois Freres (TFF)  : The maker of wine
barrels said fiscal year 2011 profit fell to 14.4 million euros
from 15.3 million the previous year. The shares fell 0.8 percent
to 29.75 euros.  Total SA (FP)  : Chief Executive Officer Christophe de
Margerie will meet with Energy Minister  Francois Baroin  to
discuss the company’s plan to raise gas prices. The shares
dropped 1.6 percent to 39.33 euros.  Volkswagen AG (VOW)  : Europe’s largest carmaker posted
first-half group sales of more than 4 million vehicles, Chief
Executive Officer  Martin Winterkorn  said at an event in Berlin.
Volkswagen shares declined 2.8 percent to 129.50 euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
